        <div class="col-md-9 nohighlight member-container">
            <h2 class="memberLink col-md-9" id="member-link-9ef9324b-744b-4210-b6b2-fff4fc0b42c0">
                Sir H. Lucas-Tooth
            </h2>
        </div>
            <div class="col-md-3 hidden-sm hidden-xs right-column ">
            <a href="#contribution-9ef9324b-744b-4210-b6b2-fff4fc0b42c0" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
               data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
               data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1950-03-14/debates/bd93d257-be42-4f0d-86bc-f5214473e055/SupplementaryEstimates#contribution-9ef9324b-744b-4210-b6b2-fff4fc0b42c0">
                <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div><span class="share-text">Share</span>
            </a>
        </div>

    


    <div class="inner">
        <div class="col-md-9 contribution content-container">



<p class="">I am much obliged to the right hon. Gentleman. When we come forward today and criticise the Government for bringing forward Supplementary Estimates for no less than £150 million, and suggest that if those Estimates had not already been spent there would have been that much more available either towards the reduction of expenditure or for the building of houses, I think we meet the right hon. Gentleman's case.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
